%YAML 1.1
%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 1cb8db85de55fa142bafb539466ab76c, type: 3}
  m_Name: TutorialDatabase
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  entries:
  - triggerKey: game_start
    message: Welcome to <i>Incinder!</i>\nYou are a Seeker, sent alone into the depths
      of this Cathedral to retrieve an ancient blood goblet. Traverse its crumbling
      rooms. Loot chests for helpful items. Face the creatures that lurk within...
      Use the shadows to your advantage, harness blood magic to overcome those who
      stand in your way and find the goblet, and your mission is complete.\n<b>Left-click</b>
      anywhere to move.
  - triggerKey: first_move
    message: You're on the move!\nOutside of combat you can move freely but in combat
      you can only move so far on your turn. Want to investigate the room without
      moving? Use <b>WASD</b> to move the camera, and hold <b>right-click</b> to
      pivot it.
  - triggerKey: first_ability_selected
    message: Abilities are your main tools in combat. Press <b>1, 2, or 3, or click
      the buttons</b> at the bottom to select one, then click a target/area to cast
      it. Hover over the ability buttons to learn each ability's details. To cancel
      targeting, press the same ability key again or switch to a different one.
  - triggerKey: first_attack
    message: Good job, you got them!\nBefore confirming a target during combat, you
      can press <b>Space</b> to <i>gamble</i> a coin flip. Success boosts the ability's
      damage by 50%, but failure halves it. You can see enemy health by hovering
      over them, or at the top of the screen in combat.
  - triggerKey: first_spotted
    message: You've been spotted!\nThe enemy is on their way to destroy you. Next
      time try staying in the shadows to slip past undetected, or strike first before
      they see you to get the drop on them.
  - triggerKey: first_combat
    message: Combat has begun!\nThe coins at the bottom right are your Action Points
      - spend them to use your abilities. You can see how far you can move each turn
      based of the line from you to your mouse.
  - triggerKey: first_damage_taken
    message: You took a hit!\nKeep an eye on your health in the bottom left. If it
      reaches zero, your quest is over, that's a complete reset back to the very
      beginning.
  - triggerKey: first_chest_open
    message: You found some items!\nSelect one of 3 options to take with you. After,
      press <b>Tab</b> or click the bag icon in the bottom right to open your inventory,
      where you can click items to equip or unequip them. You can only have 5 items
      equipped at a time.
  - triggerKey: first_combat_win
    message: Victory!\nKeep exploring, somewhere in these ruins lies a powerful artifact,
      and it won't find itself. If things get too dangerous, try stealthing through
      the shadows to slip past enemies undetected. Good luck on your quest!
